                <h2>4. Trust Your Instincts and Stay Alert</h2>
                <p>If there is one safety rule you should stick to when you travel, it is to trust your instincts. If something seems off, recognize the situation and pull yourself out of it. Gut feelings can be a very strong early warning system, especially when learning to find your way through a place you don't know much about.</p>
